  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to demonstrate that the Maestro hand held heart monitor can
      accurately diagnose Atrial Fibrillation, atrial flutter or normal sinus rhythm in patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if Maestro can be used to detect heart
      arrhythmias, specifically atrial fibrillation in humans. Maestro will be used to measure
      heart rate and rhythm at the same time that patients are being monitored with a standard 3,
      5, or 12 lead electrocardiogram (ECG) in a clinical setting. The recorded Maestro results
      will be compared to the ECG results to assess Maestro's accuracy.

      Data will be analyzed by a pass/fail criterial. The data will be downloaded and printed for
      the investigators' interpretation who will first review and code the data from Meastro,
      blinded to the ECG findings. Then the investigators will interpret the ECG findings and the
      2 sets of data will be compared. The ECG result is the true value with which to compare the
      Maestro result.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
